choices.text:
having one ‘birthday’ rather than two like some of my compatriots.

Having two birthdays is really not a problem. I myself have five birthdays; the ones when I celebrated my birth while my mom was pregnant with me: Christmas, New Years Eve, New Years Day, my birthday, and “some days after” my birth day. Having one birthday a year is not any big deal, really. What’s an ideal birthday? Does it need to be big and messy or quite and meaningful?

Comment – second paragraph: “just some of the things that people expect from a birthday… Is this a joke? you act like birthdays and gift giving have any real or philosophical meaning behind them beyond throwing a party and receiving stuff. What stuff? Its always things and hand-outs and presents people you don’t ask for. other peoples views and ideas of what should be given to you.
